comment: Duncan (SAS) sets the screen on Paul (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

RATR shows that Johnson (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Leonard's (SAS) drive and shot attempt. Any contact as Johnson swipes down is incidental as the "hand is considered part of the ball."
Johnson (LAC) makes incidental contact with Leonard (SAS) that does not affect his RSBQ at the start of the drive.
Parker (SAS) and Paul (LAC) make incidental contact with one another at the start of the drive.
Griffin (LAC) grabs Parker (SAS) and affects his RSBQ at the start of the drive.
Paul (LAC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Parker's (SAS) drive and shot attempt.
Parker (SAS) gives Redick (LAC) room to land on the jump shot.
Paul (LAC) commits a take foul on Leonard (SAS).
Aldridge (SAS) makes contact with Paul (LAC) that affects his RSBQ. The foul occurs prior to the start of Paul's upward shooting motion.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Jordan (LAC) was overturned. Los Angeles was awarded possession.
Jordan (LAC) commits a take foul on Leonard (SAS).
Paul (LAC) commits a take foul on Aldridge (SAS).
